stylometry: Aggregate Planning is when you want to make the supply of a product come as close as possible to the demand for the product. It allows you to minimize costs associated with producing revenue. You need to consider holding costs and production costs mainly. The goal of it is to produce just enough of a product so that you do not have too much inventory which would give you high holding costs. The tradeoffs are if demands shoots up suddenly you need to be able to adapt to that and be able to have enough on-hand to meet it or be able to up production costs to meet it so you must be prepared for that sceniario without losing money.
